\subtree{
\title{XBOW Resilience Notes}
\p{When caching macOS security updates on trading infrastructure:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Tier 1} (no web surface): Apple Content Caching, Reposado}
\li{\strong{Tier 2} (managed surface): Jamf DDM Blueprints}
\li{\strong{Tier 3} (large surface): JFrog Artifactory}
}

\p{Principle: dumb caches + Apple crypto signatures beat smart dashboards against autonomous AI pentesters.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Other DEX Jurisdiction Patterns}
\p{When checking any DEX, look for:}

\ol{
\li{Terms of Use → "Restricted Person" definition}
\li{Usually: US + OFAC sanctioned countries + specific conflict zones}
\li{Most Arbitrum/Base DEXs follow similar patterns to Ostium}
\li{DeFiLlama for volume/TVL comparison: \code{https://defillama.com/protocol/ostium}}
}
}
